    tf.reset_default_graph()
    # Load the benchmarking tasks
    config = Config()
    config.batch_size = 1000
    iters = 500
    # all_words_counts_unsorted, _ = get_data(config)
    # training_manager = get_training_manager(config, all_words_counts_unsorted, ['example_train.tfrecords'], "benchmarking_data")
    fnames = ["example_train.tfrecords"]
    feature_definition = {
      config.token_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((1), tf.string), # Negative
      config.positive_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((1), tf.string) # Positive
    } 
    def parser(record):
        # Parser function to be mapped to each record
        feature_definition = {
            config.token_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((), tf.string), # Negative
            config.positive_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((), tf.string) # Positive
        } 
        parsed = tf.parse_single_example(record, feature_definition)
        return parsed[config.token_key], parsed[config.positive_key]
    # Parse the loaded tfrecords
    dataset = tf.contrib.data.TFRecordDataset(fnames)
    dataset = dataset.map(parser)
    # dataset = dataset.shuffle(buffer_size=10000)
    dataset = dataset.batch(config.batch_size)
    # dataset = dataset.repeat(1000)
    iterator = dataset.make_one_shot_iterator()
    token_sample, positive_sample = iterator.get_next()
    step = 0
    global_step = tf.Variable(0, name='global_step', trainable=False, dtype=tf.int32)
    global_step_increment = self.global_step.assign_add(1)
    def thread(sess):
        # A single thread of the training
        while True:
          sess.run([global_step_increment, token_samples, positive_sample])
    with tf.Session() as sess:
        sess.run([
            tf.local_variables_initializer(), 
            tf.global_variables_initializer(), 
            tf.tables_initializer()])
        # Train the model
        workers = []
        for i in range(self.concurrent_steps):
          t = threading.Thread(target = lambda: thread(sess))
          t.start()
          workers.append(t)
        last_words = 0
        last_time = time.time()
        while True:
          time.sleep(5)  # Reports our progress once a while.
          num_words = step*self.embedding_manager.batch_size
          now = time.time()
          last_words, last_time, rate = num_words, now, (num_words - last_words) / (
            now - last_time)
          print("Step {}: words/sec = {}".format(step, rate))

    config = Config()
    all_words_counts_unsorted, fnames = get_data(config)
    feature_definition = {
      config.token_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((1), tf.string), # Negative
      config.positive_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((1), tf.string) # Positive
    } 
    def parser(record):
        # Parser function to be mapped to each record
        feature_definition = {
            config.token_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((), tf.string), # Negative
            config.positive_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((), tf.string) # Positive
        } 
        parsed = tf.parse_single_example(record, feature_definition)
        return parsed[config.token_key], parsed[config.positive_key]
    # Parse the loaded tfrecords
    dataset = tf.contrib.data.TFRecordDataset(fnames, compression_type="GZIP")
    dataset = dataset.map(parser)
    dataset = dataset.shuffle(buffer_size=10000)
    dataset = dataset.batch(config.batch_size)
    dataset = dataset.repeat(1000)
    iterator = dataset.make_one_shot_iterator()
    token_sample, positive_sample = iterator.get_next()
    !rm example_train.tfrecords
    train_filename = 'example_train.tfrecords'  # address to save the TFRecords file
    # open the TFRecords file
    writer = tf.python_io.TFRecordWriter(train_filename)
    with tf.Session() as sess:
        sess.run([
            tf.local_variables_initializer(), 
            tf.global_variables_initializer(), 
            tf.tables_initializer()])
        for i in tqdm(range(100000)):
            # Load the image
            tkn, pos = sess.run([token_sample, positive_sample])
            for t, p in zip(tkn, pos):
                feature = {config.token_key: tf.train.Feature(bytes_list=tf.train.BytesList(value=[t])), 
                           config.positive_key: tf.train.Feature(bytes_list=tf.train.BytesList(value=[p]))}
                # Create an example protocol buffer
                example = tf.train.Example(features=tf.train.Features(feature=feature))
                # Serialize to string and write on the file
                writer.write(example.SerializeToString())
    writer.close()

    class AnalogiesTask(object):
      TASK_NAME = "analogies_task"
      NUM_NEIGHBORS = 5
      def __init__(self, base_path):
        """
        Initialize the task data
        Input:
            base_path (string): The path to the benchmarking data
        """
        self.load_data(base_path)
      def load_data(self, base_path):
        """
        Load the data for this task
        """
        self.analogies = []
        with open("{}/analogies-other.txt".format(base_path)) as f:
            for line in f.readlines():
                if " " in line:
                    w1, w2, w3, w4 = line.replace("\n", "").split(" ")
                    self.analogies.append((w1, w2, w3, w4))
                    
        
      def run_task(self, word_to_embeddings):
        """
        Execute this task on the input embeddings
        """
        
        # Remove the non-word embeddings to even the playing field
        word_to_embeddings_filt = {
          k:v for k, v in word_to_embeddings.items() if k.isalpha()}
        words = list(word_to_embeddings_filt.keys())
        embeddings = np.vstack(word_to_embeddings_filt.values())
        results = {}
        # Load the analogies into query words and targets
        query_words = []
        target_embedding_diffs = []
        target_words = []
        included = 0
        for w1, w2, w3, w4 in self.analogies:
          if all([w in word_to_embeddings for w in [w1, w2, w3, w4]]):
            included += 1
            embd_diff = (word_to_embeddings[w2] - 
                         word_to_embeddings[w1] + 
                         word_to_embeddings[w3])
            query_words.append((w1,w2,w3))
            target_embedding_diffs.append(embd_diff)
            target_words.append(w4)
        results["coverage"] = float(included)/len(self.analogies)
        
        # Find the nearest neighbors
        nn = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=self.NUM_NEIGHBORS + 3, algorithm="brute", metric="cosine")
        nn.fit(embeddings)
        # Iterate through to avoid an OOM
        neighbors = []
        step = 100
        for i in tqdm(range(0, len(target_embedding_diffs), step)):
          _, chunk_neighbors = nn.kneighbors(target_embedding_diffs[i:i+step])
          neighbors += chunk_neighbors.tolist()
        correct = 0
        for target_word, neighbor_inds, qw in zip(target_words, neighbors, query_words):
          found_words = [words[ind] for ind in neighbor_inds 
                         if not words[ind] in query_words][:self.NUM_NEIGHBORS]
          correct += any([words[ind] == target_word for ind in neighbor_inds])
        results["accuracy"] = float(correct)/float(len(neighbors))
        return results
    . . .

    def parser(record):
        feature_definition = {

          positive_key: tf.FixedLenFeature((), tf.string) # Positive

    total = 0
    with tf.Session() as sess:
        coord = tf.train.Coordinator()
        threads = tf.train.start_queue_runners(coord = coord)     
        sess.run([tf.local_variables_initializer(), tf.global_variables_initializer(), tf.tables_initializer()])
        tkn, pos = sess.run([token_id, positive_id])
        start = time.time()
        for i in range(1000):
            tkn, pos = sess.run([token_id, positive_id])
            total += tkn.shape[0] 
        total_time = time.time() - start
        coord.request_stop()
        coord.join(threads)

    normalized_embeddings_dict = {w:e/np.linalg.norm(e) 
                  for w, e in zip(embeddings["words"], embeddings["embd_values"]) if not np.all(np.isclose(e, 0))}
    results = {}
    for tsv, name in [(men, "men"), (rw, "rw"), (wordsim353, "wordsim353")]:
        embd_pairs = [(normalized_embeddings_dict.get(w1, None), 
                       normalized_embeddings_dict.get(w2, None),
                       sim) for w1, w2, sim in zip(tsv["w1"], tsv["w2"], tsv["sim"])]
        embd_pairs_filtered =  [(e1, e2, sim) for e1, e2, sim in embd_pairs 
                                if ((e1 is not None) and (e2 is not None))]
        embd_vector_sims = [np.dot(e1, e2) for e1, e2, _ in embd_pairs_filtered]
        embd_human_sims  = [sim for _, _, sim in embd_pairs_filtered]
        results[name] = {}
        results[name]["corr"] = pearsonr(embd_vector_sims, embd_human_sims)[0]
        results[name]["coverage"] = float(len(embd_pairs_filtered)/len(embd_pairs))
    for name, v in results.items():
        print(name, v["corr"], v["coverage"])
